sentences: David Buskin (born December 13, 1943 in New York City) is a singer, songwriter, performer, author, playwright, jingle composer and girls' basketball coach.
He is well known for composing numerous television and radio commercials produced in the 1980s and 1990s.
He won a Clio Award in 1983 for Just Watch Us Now, NBC's signature jingle.
